<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1447,1797]" pageId="3" pageNumber="581">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,368,1590,1616]" pageId="3" pageNumber="581">Identification.</emphasis>
This species was identified from keys, descriptions, and illustrations found in the publications by 
<bibRefCitation author="Denning, D. G. &amp; Blickle, R. L." box="[151,449,1627,1653]" pageId="3" pageNumber="581" pagination="27 - 33" refId="ref5366" refString="Denning, D. G. &amp; Blickle, R. L. (1979) New species of Helicopsyche (Trichoptera: Helicopsychidae). Pan-Pacific Entomologist, 55, 27 - 33." type="journal article" year="1979">Denning &amp; Blickle (1979)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Johanson, K. A." box="[461,641,1627,1653]" pageId="3" pageNumber="581" pagination="1 - 147" refId="ref5966" refString="Johanson, K. A. (2002) Systematic revision ofAmerican Helicopsyche of the subgenus Feropsyche (Trichoptera, Helicopsychidae). Insect Systematics &amp; Evolution Supplement, 60, 1 - 147." type="journal article" year="2002">Johanson (2002</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Johanson, K. A." box="[652,712,1627,1653]" pageId="3" pageNumber="581" pagination="1 - 12" refId="ref6001" refString="Johanson, K. A. (2003) The Helicopsyche (Feropsyche) (Insecta, Trichoptera, Helicopsychidae) from Barro Colorado Island, Panama. Zootaxa, 283 (1), 1 - 12. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 283.1.1" type="journal article" year="2003">2003</bibRefCitation>
), 
<bibRefCitation author="Johanson, K. A. &amp; Malm, T." box="[732,1024,1627,1653]" pageId="3" pageNumber="581" pagination="1 - 24" refId="ref6052" refString="Johanson, K. A. &amp; Malm, T. (2006) Seven new Helicopsyche (Feropsyche) Johanson, 2002 from the Neotropical region and Nearctic Mexico (Insecta: Trichoptera: Helicopsychidae). Zootaxa, 1208 (1), 1 - 24. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 1208.1.1" type="journal article" year="2006">Johanson &amp; Malm (2006)</bibRefCitation>
, and 
<bibRefCitation author="Johanson, K. A. &amp; Holzenthal, R. W." box="[1084,1433,1627,1653]" pageId="3" pageNumber="581" pagination="37 - 47" refId="ref6113" refString="Johanson, K. A. &amp; Holzenthal, R. W. (2010) The snail-case caddisfly subgenus Helicopsyche (Feropsyche) in Costa Rica, with the description of 3 new species (Trichoptera: Helicopsychidae). Zootaxa, 2689, 37 - 47." type="journal article" year="2010">Johanson &amp; Holzenthal (2010)</bibRefCitation>
. This species, based on the boomerang-shaped inferior appendages, bears a slight resemblance to 
<taxonomicName authority="Ross 1956" authorityName="Ross" authorityYear="1956" class="Insecta" family="Helicopsychidae" genus="Helicopsyche" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="581" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vergelana">
<emphasis box="[1230,1375,1663,1689]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="581">H. vergelana</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Ross, H. H." pageId="3" pageNumber="581" pagination="397 - 401" refId="ref6670" refString="Ross, H. H. (1956) New species of Helicopsyche from the western hemisphere (Trichoptera, Helicopsychidae). Journal of the Washington Academy of Sciences, 46 (12), 397 - 401." type="journal article" year="1956">Ross 1956</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. It differs from this and other species by the ventrad-directed tergum X and the overall shape of the inferior appendages in lateral and dorsal views, each with the distal portion &lt;1.5X as broad as its distal portion in lateral view.
</paragraph>
